contentrichtext.text: '''Voigt''' (mainly written [[Vogt]], also Voight) is a German surname, and may refer to: * [[Angela Voigt]], East German long jumper * [[Alexander Voigt]], German football player * [[Christian August Voigt]] (1808-1890), Austrian anatomist * [[Cynthia Voigt]], author of books for young adults * [[Deborah Voigt]], American opera singer * [[Edward Voigt]], born in Bremen, Germany, former U.S. Representative from Wisconsin * [[Edwin Edgar Voigt]], Bischop * [[Ellen Bryant Voigt]], German American poet * [[Erika Voigt]], actress * [[Frederick Augustus Voigt]] (1892–1957), British journalist and author of German descent * [[Wilhelm Voigt]] (1849–1922), the "Hauptmann von Köpenick", German impostor * [[Georg Voigt]], German historian * [[Harry Voigt]], German Olympic athlete * [[Jack Voigt]], baseball player * [[Jan Voigt]], actor * [[Jens Voigt]], professional road cyclist * [[Joachim Otto Voigt]], a Danish and German botanist * [[Johannes Voigt]], German historian and father of Georg(e) * [[Philip Nolan Voigt]], fictional character from Marvel Comics * [[Stu Voigt]], former NFL tight end * [[Udo Voigt]], German ultra-conservative politician * [[Werner Voigt]], German football coach and former player * [[Woldemar Voigt]] (1850–1919), German physicist * [[Wolfgang Voigt]], electronic music artist ==See also== * The [[Voigt profile]], a peak function * The [[Voigt pipe]], a type of loudspeaker * [[Voigt notation]], a way to represent [[Symmetric tensor]] * [[Voight]] * [[Vogt]] * [[Vogt (surname)]] * [[Voit (surname)]] * [[Kelvin–Voigt material]] {{surname}}<!-- It does not help to add disambig or hndis tags where the page only contains people who share a surname --> [[Category:German-language surnames]] [[Category:Occupational surnames]]
